               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18480515-name-1418" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18480515-name-1418" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18480515-name-1418" type="surname" value="BOORAH"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18480515-name-1418" type="given" value="THOMAS"></interp>THOMAS BOORAH.</persName>
                  </hi> I am a dealer. An order for goods had been given to the prisoner in the name of Mansfield—he brought them on Friday, 24th March, and I paid him 2<hi rend="italic">l</hi>.—he gave me this receipt—it is signed "Mansfield"—he represented himself as Mansfield—on 27th March I paid him 3<hi rend="italic">l</hi>. 11<hi rend="italic">s</hi>. 4<hi rend="italic">d</hi>.—he represented himself as Mansfield, a nd signed the receipt Mansfield.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined by</hi> 
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MR. O'BRIEN.</hi> 
                  <hi rend="italic">Q.</hi> You gave him the order for himself? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> He brought the card—I gave him the order.</p>
               <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="184805150165"></xptr>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18480515-name-1419" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18480515-name-1419" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18480515-name-1419" type="surname" value="MANSFIELD"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18480515-name-1419" type="given" value="THOMAS"></interp>THOMAS MANSFIELD.</persName>
                  </hi> I employed the prisoner—I gave him the goods to go to Mr. Boorah—I authorised him to receive the money—he never paid me—I authorised him to receive money once before—on the Friday he received 2<hi rend="italic">l</hi>., and never accounted for it—on the Saturday he came, and had 13<hi rend="italic">s</hi>. 6<hi rend="italic">d</hi>. for his wages—I found him in a public-house tipsy—he swore he never received it.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined. Q.</hi> You did not know he had received this 2<hi rend="italic">l</hi>.? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> No—he was paid according to what he did—I gave him half-a-crown for the job—I did not go to either of the customers before the money was received—I gave him the goods to carry out with another man—the money was to be paid to him—I went with him to the house—I remained ouside—he came out, and said Mr. Boorah was not in the way—I did not go in; they did not know me, and would not pay me—the prisoner had not known them before—he told me to stay outside—he received the order, and was to execute it—he had not been at work on the other transaction above a fortnight—I am sure the goods were mine.</p>
               <p>
